The Pythagorean Theorem gives us $AC = \sqrt{BC^2 - AB^2} = \sqrt{100 - 36} = \sqrt{64}=8$, so $\cos C = \frac{AC}{BC} = \frac{8}{10} = \boxed{\frac45}$. The answer is \frac45.

[asy]
