2h^2 & = 150^2 + 130^2 - 140^2 \\
2h^2 & = 19800 \\
h^2 & = 9900\\
h & = \sqrt{9900}=30\sqrt{11}
\end{align*} Therefore, the height of the balloon above the field is $\boxed{30\sqrt{11}}$ meters. The answer is 30\sqrt{11}.

